statement.p:
Assume n \geq 2.  If a_i, i = 1, 2, \dots, n are non-negative real numbers, then
\left(a_1a_2\cdots  a_n\right){}^{1/n}\leq  \frac{a_1+a_2+\cdots +a_n}{n}
with equality if and only if all the a_i are equal.

Prove that a list can be made of all the subsets of a finite set such that


the empty set is the first set;

each subset occurs once;

each subset is obtained from the preceding by adding or deleting an element.
